	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Nov 14th 8:03 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=107517><span id= >Muvyn</span></a><br><span id=notbold>57 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.05]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>While testing this thing with Melody of Ervaj, I found that I could NOT strike my target at all while I had the MoE buff on. Once the buff fades I begin striking my target again. Anyone else experiencing this? Let it be known that I have only used the weapon against sub-level 50 NPC's thus far. Any information would be useful!&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>EQ1 -<br>Crusadis Honorblade - 66 Warrior of Quellious (ret.)<br>Zilendar Psytosis - 66 Enchanter of Quellious (ret.)<br>Muvyn Fastur - 52 Bard of Quellious (ret.)<br>Noros Inuvik - 51 Druid of Quellious (ret.)<br>Kaitak Sunfists - 50 Monk of Quellious (ret.)<br><br>EQ2 - <br>Kindle - 18 Crusader of Lavastorm<br>Instar - 8 Mage of Lucan D'Lere</td></tr>
