<tr><td colspan=2><ul>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f105146273329044>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=16448&mid=105146273329044>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=16448&mid=105146273329044>RE: Trouble Melee'ing with Ervaj???</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=16448&mid=105146273329044#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Apr 27th 1:37 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=223387><span id= >Mandallin</span></a><br><span id=notbold>9 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I think people get confused with the Battlecry/Warcry of the Vah Shir line of songs.&nbsp;&nbsp;People say they &quot;stack&quot; with everything, but it's not actually haste.  The songs increase the haste cap.<br>I.e: Haste cap pre 50 is 50%.  Say someone has SCHW (22% haste) and Celerity (50% haste) they stack to 77% haste.  The cap, however, doesn't let them exceed 50% haste.  Now say there is a bard in the group playing Battlecry of the Vah Shir; the song is estimated to increase the haste cap by about 15-25%.  Now the person with 77% haste can actually use 65-75% (the new haste cap) of it.<br><br>Hope this didn't get too confusing.  If you learn anything from this, I hope you learn that the Battlecry/Warcry of the Vah Shir songs don't &quot;add&quot; haste, they &quot;increase the haste cap.&quot;<br><br>Edit: This is in response to a reply someone made below me.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Apr 27 13:01:14 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Mandallin<br></td></tr>
